# iOS device preview — who dat (2)

When changing the Warmth iOS app, **build and install on the connected iPhone** so Amir can preview on device — not only the simulator.

## Target device

- **Name:** `who dat (2)`
- **Model:** iPhone 17
- If it is **available (paired)** in `xcrun devicectl list devices`, deploy there.
- If offline/unavailable, build simulator as fallback and note that the phone was not connected.

## After iOS changes

From `iOS/Warmth-iOS/`:

```bash
# Build
xcodebuild build -scheme Warmth \
  -destination 'platform=iOS,name=who dat (2)' \
  -allowProvisioningUpdates \
  -derivedDataPath /tmp/warmth-ios-dd

# Install + launch
APP="/tmp/warmth-ios-dd/Build/Products/Debug-iphoneos/Warmth.app"
xcrun devicectl device install app --device "who dat (2)" "$APP"
xcrun devicectl device process launch --device "who dat (2)" com.warmth.gtmhackathon
```

Run `xcodegen generate` first if `project.yml` changed.

## Do not

- Skip device deploy when the phone is connected and the task touched iOS UI or behavior Amir would preview.
- Force-push or change signing team without asking.
